# ErgNet — Cline Rules

# For the complete agent guide, see docs/agent-instructions.md

## Project

- .NET 10 library (`net10.0`) for Concept2 PM3/PM4/PM5 ergometer communication
- NuGet package: `ErgNet` | Root namespace: `ErgNet` | Solution: `ErgNet.slnx`
- "ErgNet" = the library; "Concept2" = the hardware manufacturer (never swap them)

## Commands

- Build: `dotnet build --configuration Release`
- Test: `dotnet test tests/ErgNet.Tests/ErgNet.Tests.csproj --logger "console;verbosity=detailed"`
- Pack: `dotnet pack --configuration Release --output ./nupkg`
- All warnings are errors (`TreatWarningsAsErrors` enabled)

## Code Style

- File-scoped namespaces: `namespace ErgNet;`
- `var` when type is apparent; expression-bodied members for one-liners
- 4-space indentation, LF line endings, UTF-8
- Sort usings with `System` first; follow `.editorconfig`
- All public types/members require XML doc comments
- Use `<inheritdoc />` on interface implementations

## Patterns

- Async/await with `CancellationToken` on all I/O methods
- `IAsyncEnumerable<T>` with `[EnumeratorCancellation]` for streaming
- `SemaphoreSlim` guards concurrent transport access
- `Channel<T>` merges BLE notification streams
- `ObjectDisposedException.ThrowIf` at start of public methods
- `ArgumentNullException.ThrowIfNull` for null checks
- Transport abstraction: users implement `IHidDevice`/`IBleDevice`/`IAntDevice`

## Testing

- xUnit 2.9.3 with `MethodName_Scenario_ExpectedBehavior` naming
- Hand-written fakes over mocking frameworks
- `using Xunit;` is global via `.csproj` — do not add to test files
- Byte-level comments in protocol tests; test paths mirror source paths

## Architecture

- Unified `IPerformanceMonitor` API regardless of transport
- USB: CSAFE polling | BLE: GATT notifications | ANT+: FE-C broadcasts (receive-only)
- PM commands wrapped in `SetUserCfg1` (0x1A); multiple coalesced under single wrapper
- ANT+ uses 8-bit rollover counters (`RolloverCounterMax = 256`)

## Error Handling

- `ArgumentException` for invalid configs
- `NotSupportedException` for unsupported transport operations (e.g., CSAFE over ANT+)
- `InvalidOperationException` for state errors
- `CsafeFrameException` for protocol errors

## Versioning

- GitVersion 6.x + Conventional Commits (feat: = minor, fix: = patch, feat!: = major)
- main → `alpha`, release/* → `rc`, production → stable (via manual promote)
- No hardcoded version in `.csproj`
